The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, July 10: Leading industrialist Bharat Ram, the chairman emeritus of DCM Ltd and SRF, died here tonight after a brief illness. He was 93. Bharat Ram is survived by his wife and three sons. Born on October 15, 1914 in Delhi, Bharat Ram was an economics graduate from St. Stephens College. He joined DCM in 1935 as an apprentice and rose to the position of chairman and managing director in 1958. He had retired from DCM in 1985.

 New Delhi, July 10: The government today asked oil companies to provide a break-up of the pricing of aviation turbine fuel within 15 days to find ways to reduce the high rates the airlines have to pay. 

 New Delhi, July 10: Better performance by steel, cement, petroleum products and electricity sectors helped six core infrastructure industries clock a year-on-year growth of 8.7 per cent in May.

 New Delhi, July 10: Sinosteel is planning to partner with Chinese steel firm Handan Zongheng Iron and Steel Group to work on its five-million-tonne steel plant in Jharkhand.

 New Delhi, July 10: The five-member committee set up by BSNL to look into the re-evaluation of a tender and help the PSU prepare a response to telecom minister A. Rajas queries is likely to submit the report tomorrow to the management.




